description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated nurse with a keen interest in the management of tuberculosis to join our established and supportive specialist nursing TB team which is expanding to meet local need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The specialist TB nursing team covers both Greenwich and Bexley community and integrates with both acute and primary care teams to provide a seamless service to support the care of people receiving TB treatment, their contacts and the wider community in accordance with nationally agreed guidelines and local protocols.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The specialist nurses provide a case management approach and actively promote best practice and highest standards in TB management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and confident first level nurse with the required post registration experience with evidence of continuing professional development which should include the TB management course and IV competency. You will need excellent clinical and communication skills and an ability to work with diverse health and social needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer you the chance to work as part of a dynamic nursing that works in primary and acute settings and as part of wider multi professional and multi agency services; develop clinical and teaching skills and participate in clinical supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Oxleas operates a probationary period, further information is available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stella Abiona, Lead Nurse TB on 020 8836 5887, stella.abiona@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
